Hong Kong  stocks  rose, with a gauge
of Chinese companies headed for its steepest gain in a month.  The  Hang Seng China Enterprises Index (HSCEI)  of mainland companies
rose 1.1 percent to 8,969.93 as of 9:37 a.m. in Hong Kong. The
benchmark  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  rose 0.4 percent to 19,936.7.  To contact the reporter on this story:
